HIT ME ONE MORE TIME

Blackjack has always been a hugely popular game, not just in real casinos but also in the live dealer casino. It’s a bit of a mystery as to why it’s still called Blackjack. Based on the game of 21, which had been played at various levels since the 16th century, the modern game was perfected in the USA. Riverboats and saloons made perfect casinos, but with so many venues to choose from, many establishments felt they needed to offer a little more in order to attract customers.
That’s where the black jack came in. A side bet was offered whereby if a player was dealt an Ace of Spades along with a black-suited Jack, they won a 10-1 bonus. By all accounts, this was a short-lived promotion, either because nefarious dealers would remove such cards from the deck or because the combination hit too many times for the offer to remain viable. But the name stuck. It would be a bit like calling Monopoly ‘Buy One, Get One Free’ because a supermarket once offered a deal on the board game.
While the blackjack deal may not have lasted too long, the concept of side bets and offers remains a part of the game, even at a live casino online. Like the original blackjack, many of them are based around the cards that you are dealt. For example, Perfect Pairs is a sidebet that you can place on several of our Blackjack games. If you are dealt two of the exact same card, such as two of the Ace of Hearts, you can win a bonus. Do not be perturbed by the fact that you’re looking at more than one of the same card – remember that Blackjack is a multideck game!
Another popular sidebet is 21+3, which again follows the same rules, but this one includes the single face-up card that the dealer has in order to make a three-card hand. Suited trips, mixed trips, a 3-card straight or a 3-card flush could all net you a bonus if you wager on it before the cards are dealt.

WELL PLAYED, MR BOND

James Bond’s favourite game can also be found in our live casino online – Baccarat. It’s another game that has been played since the Middle Ages and has lasted because of its simplicity and fairness. It’s very difficult to cheat at Baccarat (but not impossible as we’ll see later) because the player bets on whether their hand or the banker’s will win. You cannot really rig one hand to be better than another when you do not know which one a player is going to choose.
